HEADWORD: Breezy
<hw>Breez"y</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Characterized by, or having, breezes; airy.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>breezy</xex> day in May.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'Mid lawns and shades by <qex>breezy</qex> rivulets fanned.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fresh; brisk; full of life.</def>
